Congratulations to Brooklyn Turpin and Mary Flint for having their art accepted in the Springville Museum of Art Christmas Lamb Show. We are pleased to have these students represent our school.

Opening Reception
All students accepted into the show and their families are invited to an Opening Reception on Saturday, December 3, 2016 from 12:00 - 1:00 pm in the Atrium (main level) of the Springville Museum of Art.

Awards Ceremony
Award winners will be recognized December 3, 2016 from 11:00 am ‚Äì 12:00 pm in the Grand Gallery (upper level) of the Springville Museum of Art. Students receiving an award will be notified a week or so before the Awards Ceremony.

post_text:
Congratulations to the following Renaissance Students for being accepted into the Springville Museum of Art's Christmas Lamb Exhibit:
Brooklyn Turpin, 3rd
Haley Burnah, 1st
Madeline Burnah, 3rd

Opening Receptio
All students accepted into the show are invited to an Opening Reception on Saturday, December 5, 2015 from 11:00am - 1:00pm in the Atrium (main level) of the Springville Museum of Art.

30th Annual Christmas Lamb Show
December 5, 2015 - January 3, 2016
See Christmas through the eyes of a child. This annual juried exhibition showcases the art of school-age children from around Utah County. post_text:
Las Posadas has been a tradition in Mexico for over 400 years. The Spanish Department at Renaissance Academy wishes to invite our Spanish students and their families to join us in celebrating this great cultural event.

We will have a program for you to enjoy with authentic performances, such as: students reenacting Las Posadas; listening to Spanish holiday carols; admiring the students‚Äô homemade pi√±atas; and of course, enjoying hot chocolate and churros.

Where: 3435 N 1120 E, Lehi, UT 84043
When: Thursday, December 18, 2014 at 6:00pm.

post_text: Please donate to RA's Food Drive, going on now through October 18th! Our goal is 1,565 pounds - if each RA family donates 5 lbs, we will exceed our goal by more than 500 pounds! We already have over 400 pounds! Please donate non-perishable food items such as canned meat, vegetables, fruit, beans, boxed cereal, boxed meals, 100% fruit juice, Mac'n'Cheese, etc. The food donated will go to the Community Services Food Bank out of Provo, Utah, which helps out the struggling Utahns in Utah County.

Renaissance Academy added 7 new photos.
October 7, 2013 at 9:36 AM ¬∑

We went to the BYU Athletic Communications office where we talked to Sports Information Director, Kyle Chilton, who told us what they produce in their office for the Athletics Department. We also went up to the graphic design studio where Dave Broberg taught them more about how they use Photoshop, InDesign, and other programs (which the students have been learning) to produce their posters, signs, etc.

Lastly, we went to the 3rd floor of the football stadium, where the press box is, and they were able to see where the photographers and journalists sit at a game. They were told what happens in the box during the game. And before we came back to the school they took some pictures on the field and got to run around. :)

post_text: Mr. Gomaa and the Bedouin Fair featured on the TCLP website : )
shared_text:
Teachers of Critical Languages Program - TCLP is with Nader Mounir Nielsen and 3 others.
April 24, 2013 at 9:47 AM ¬∑

Munir Gomaa was in the spotlight last Saturday, April 20, as his school put on a huge event called "From Sinai to Salt Lake City: A Bedouin Fair". Renaissance Academy received a TCLP Project Grant to sponsor the fair which helped build awareness and understanding of the Bedouin and Arabic culture and language. Over 400 people attended the fair and participated in many hands-on activities including making Bedouin bread and cooking it over a fire, getting painted with Henna, trying on Bedouin clothing, interacting with animals (goats and camels), dancing, drumming, eating, and even climbing a 24ft. Mt. Sinai climbing wall. It was a great success and everyone has had enthusiastic things to say about it. It is the biggest event the World Language team has sponsored at Renaissance, and Arabic language students from two other high schools also came to support the event.

Article Credit: Stacy Lyon

Renaissance Academy had the opportunity to host a group of performing arts students from China. These students were here as part of an outreach program sponsored by Celebrating Children: U.S. and China, a Utah non-profit organization.

During their visit, students stayed with Renaissance Academy host families, participating in school day activities, enjoying a Chinese New Year dinner with host families, and performing an assembly of traditional Chinese music and dance at Renaissance Academy and Orem High School.

post_text: A warm welcome to you.
shared_text:
Save the Space Center
March 24, 2013 at 12:35 PM ¬∑

We are extremely excited to announce our partnership with Renaissance Academy in Lehi to Save The Space Center.

We will be making presentation to the community on the future of the 'Farpoint Institute' (aka new Space Center Programs) on Wednesday April 17, 2013 at 7:00 PM at Renaissance Academy.

Press is welcome to attend the event on Wednesday evening. Exclusive media interview time will be held from 6:45-7:00pm.
